        <p class="about-text">
          The "Johnny Johnny Yes Papa" story is a simple, well-known English-language nursery rhyme and children's song.
          It follows a basic call-and-response structure between a child (Johnny) and a parent (usually the father, “Papa”).
          The story’s meaning and context goes like this:<br><br>
          • Johnny is a mischievous little boy.<br>
          • Papa suspects Johnny is doing something he’s not supposed to (e.g., eating sugar).<br>
          • Johnny denies it.<br>
          • When Papa asks him to "open his mouth," Johnny laughs—implying he was indeed sneaking sugar and got caught.
        </p>
